{
  "texts": [
    "During training, the network incrementally learns the value of each parameter that best predicts the output from a given input.",
    "Also, during training the backpropagation algorithm incrementally adjusts all the model parameters in a direction that gradually decreases the error with each training iteration.",
    "A differentiable loss function of the error enables the backpropagation algorithm to compute gradients.",
    "That is, a derivative of the loss function with respect to a parameter produces a gradient that tells the algorithm the direction to adjust that parameter to reduce the error.",
    "The derivative uses the chain rule of calculus to propagate parameter adjustments backwards from the output."
  ]
}